#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is an operating system?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Linux, UNIX, BSD, Windows, and MacOS are all **operating systems**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:33
#: ../src/docs/guides/contribute/rockydocs_formatting.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "!!! abstract\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "    An operating system is a **set of programs that manages the available resources of a computer**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "As part of this management of resources, the operating system has to:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage the **physical** or **virtual** memory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **physical memory** is made up of the RAM bars and the processor cache memory, which are used for the execution of programs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **virtual memory** is a location on the hard disk (the **swap** partition) that allows the unloading of the physical memory and the saving of the current state of the system during the electrical shutdown of the computer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Intercept **access to peripherals**.\n"
"Software is rarely allowed to access hardware directly (except for graphics cards for very specific needs).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Provide applications with proper **task management**.\n"
"The operating system is responsible for scheduling processes to occupy the processor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Protect files** from unauthorized access.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Collect information** about programs in use or in progress.\n"
msgstr ""

