msgid "A user of a Microsoft or Mac operating system must purchase a license to use the operating system. This license has a cost, although it is usually transparent (the price of the license is included in the price of the computer).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:196
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the **GNU/Linux** world, the Free Software movement provides mostly free distributions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Free** does not mean free!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:200
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Open Source**: the source code is available, so it is possible to consult and modify it under certain conditions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "A free software is necessarily open-source, but the opposite is not true since open-source software is distinct from the freedom offered by the GPL license.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "GNU GPL (GNU General Public License)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:206
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **GPL** guarantees the author of a software its intellectual property, but allows modification, redistribution or resale of software by third parties, provided that the source code is included with the software. The GPL is the license that came out of the **GNU** (GNU is Not UNIX) project, which was instrumental in creating Linux.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:208
#, no-wrap
msgid "It implies:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "The freedom to run the program, for any purpose.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "The freedom to study how the program works and adapt it to your needs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "The freedom to redistribute copies.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "The freedom to improve the program, and publish those improvements for the benefit of the whole community.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "On the other hand, even products licensed under the GPL can have a cost. This is not for the product itself, but the **guarantee that a team of developers will continue to work on it to make it evolve and troubleshoot errors, or even provide support to users**.\n"
msgstr ""

