#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/01-presentation.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "Linux is a suitable choice for hosting databases or websites, or as a mail server, DNS or firewall. In short, Linux can do just about anything, which explains the quantity of specific distributions.\n"
